### Approach 1 - Brute Force
**Time Complexity :** O(n^2)
**Space Complexity :**  O(1)
**Explanation:**
1. Iterate over array
2. Check if element is 0
3. Shift all remaining elements to right by one

**Code:**
```
class Solution {
public:
    void duplicateZeros(vector<int>& arr) {
        const int VALUE_ZERO = 0;
        const int ARRAY_LENGTH = arr.size();

        for(int i=0; i<ARRAY_LENGTH; i++){
            if(arr[i] != VALUE_ZERO)
                continue;

            for(int j=ARRAY_LENGTH-1; j>i; j--)
                arr[j] = arr[j-1];

            i++;
        }
    }
};
```

---

### Approach 2 - Queue
**Time Complexity :** O(n)
**Space Complexity :**  O(n)
**Explanation:**
1. Create a queue
2. Add element to queue
3. Check if element is zero
4. Then again add element to queue
5. Set frontmost elemnt of queue to array
6. Remove element from queue

**Code:**
```
class Solution {
public:
    void duplicateZeros(vector<int>& arr) {
        const int VALUE_ZERO = 0;
        const int ARRAY_LENGTH = arr.size();
        queue<int> data;

        for(int index=0; index<ARRAY_LENGTH; index++){
            data.push(arr[index]);

            if(arr[index] == VALUE_ZERO)
                data.push(arr[index]);

            arr[index] = data.front();
            data.pop();
        }
    }
};
```

---

### Approach 3 - Two Pointers
**Time Complexity :** O(n)
**Space Complexity :**  O(1)
**Explanation:**
1. Set start to 0 and end to last index
2. Iterate over array until end
3. Decrement end occurance of 0
4. Later iterate over array in reverse until end pointer
5. Set end pointer value to current
6. Set previous index to 0 on occurence of 0 if start != end

**Code:**
```
class Solution {
public:
    void duplicateZeros(vector<int>& arr) {
        const int VALUE_ZERO = 0;
        const int ARRAY_LENGTH = arr.size();

        int start = 0;
        int end = ARRAY_LENGTH-1;

        while(start < end){
            if(arr[start] == VALUE_ZERO)
                end--;
            start++;
        }

        for(int index=ARRAY_LENGTH-1; index>end; index--, end--){
            arr[index] = arr[end];

            if(arr[end] == VALUE_ZERO && start != end)
                arr[--index] = VALUE_ZERO;
        }
    }
};
```

