solutions.content:
Steps:
* First find how many elements will cover up the whole array if we duplicate 0. let, till index `i`.
* Then try to stretch the subarray `[0,i]` to the right.
[ if the value at index `i` is 0, duplicating it may exceed the array length ]

Consider the given example:
`[1,0,2,3,0,4,5,0]`, array length is 8.
								index: `0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7`
contribution in final array: `1 2 1 1 2 1 1 2`

So the  the subarray [0,5] will cover up the array of length 8.

Now, stretch the array to the right:
put value of index 
* 5 to index 7              ` [ -, -, -, -, -, -, -, 4]`
* 4 to index 6 & 5  ` [ -, -, -, -, -, 0, 0, 4]`
*  3 to index 4   `[ -, -, -, -,3, 0, 0, 4]`
*   2 to index 3   ` [ -, -, -, 2,3, 0, 0, 4]`
*   1 to index 2 & 1  ` [ -, 0, 0, 2,3, 0, 0, 4]`
*   0 to index 0   `[ 1, 0, 0, 2,3, 0, 0, 4]`

Consider another case: [1,0,2,3,0,4]
Here, stretching range [0,4] will cover the full array. But duplicating all 0 will exceed the given array length.
I handled this case manually.

Here is my solution:
